    <prj:ScienceGoal mode="Other">
        <prj:name>NaCl 21-20 torus emission</prj:name>
        <prj:note>The aim of this science goal is to map the NaCl 21-20 emission arising from the torus observed in Cycle 0 towards IRC+10216. In order to be able to resolve both spatially and spectroscopically the emission from this torus, we ask for an spectral resolution of 0.8 km/s and an angular resolution of 0.04". 

The peak line flux per beam is expected to be higher than 130 mJy. However, in order to map the weakest regions of the torus, we ask for a RMS of 0.3 mJy, which can be reached in ~35 minutes. </prj:note>
